<http://www.spektrix.com/yukonartscentre/event/64201ATQMVTPNLDTBBPSHQGLJJBVSHVRP>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Northern Tails Season 2 : Premiere Screening & Reception";
  schema:description """
	Back by popular demand, Northern Tails is set to unleash Season 2 of its puppet-powered wildlife web series and Whitehorse is invited to be the first to watch. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Step out and celebrate with the show’s creators, cast and crew (and a few famous critters) who have charmed the pants off audiences around the planet as they venture to shed light on the boreal forest – a wild and wondrous place that’s the world’s largest ecosystem. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Our evening kicks off with a “green carpet” reception that pulls back the curtain on the production sets, props, and puppets that transform the show’s storyworlds.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The premiere screening program features two new episodes and a debut performance by the boreal’s favourite froggy band – The Bogstreet Boys! It’s original entertainment with heart, smarts, and silly bits made in the Yukon, by Yukoners.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>—<span><br/></span>Presented by: Shot in the Dark Productions and Screen Production Yukon Association<span><br/></span>Funded by: Yukon Media Development, Canada Media Fund, Bell Fund, Northwestel Community TV<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Doors open: 6:00 pm<span><br/></span>Show starts: 7:00 pm</span><span><br/></span>
""";
