<http://www.spektrix.com/yukonartscentre/event/58802AMDGSDDLPVSJNMCHGHMVVSJVRRTR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Guild and Gwaandak Theatre Present: The Birds by Yvette Nolan";
  schema:description """
	The Birds by Yvette Nolan <span><br/></span>Directed by Jennifer Dawn Bishop<span><br/></span>A Guild Hall and Gwaandak Theatre Co-production<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A modern re-telling of Aristophanes’ classic comic fantasy ‘The Birds’. Two humans, frustrated by the modern world, arrive in the fabled land of the birds seeking freedom and a better way of life. Despite their best intentions they are unable to resist remaking this utopian paradise in their own image, without regard for the inhabitants who already occupy the land. Set in a richly imagined, song and dance filled land of the birds. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Join us for a drink and/or a non-alcoholic beverage before the show in the Guild Hall Pub. We have a great selection of non-alcoholic drinks!  The pub side will open its doors at 6:15pm. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">The performance on February 18th will be a Relaxed Performance.  The relaxed performance will have less intense lights and sound and will offer a more casual atmosphere to invite audience members who wish to experience a lower level of stimulation during the performance. Everyone is welcome.  If you would like more information please contact ytguildhall@gmail.com</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Thank you to our sponsors and funders: Government of Yukon, Lotteries Yukon, City of Whitehorse, Kilrich Building Centres, Whitehorse Motors, SPK Home Construction Ltd, Yukon Brewing, Northern Vision Development and Air North<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-02-27T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/yukonartscentre/files/cd7b8c9e-a8ca-44f5-a85e-dbbde37a96a8.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/yukonartscentre/location/404ALTQJTMGRQHLVHMCJNCTMNSLVDVNGH>;
  schema:offers _:ec4383dd32b74b0f85c637f958b321f82850;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-02-27T20:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

